# Example .gitignore for REST Client HTTP files
# Copy relevant sections to your project's .gitignore

# ============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT FILES - SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# ============================================================================

# Always ignore .env files (they may contain secrets)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Ignore local environment file overrides
# (Use these for personal/local configurations)
.http-client-env.local.json
http-client.env.local.json

# ============================================================================
# RECOMMENDED APPROACH
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. COMMIT the base environment file with safe defaults:
#    .http-client-env.json (with $processEnv for secrets)
#
# 2. IGNORE local overrides for personal configurations:
#    .http-client-env.local.json
#
# 3. DOCUMENT required environment variables in README
#
# Example structure:
#
# .http-client-env.json (COMMIT this):
# {
#   "$shared": { "apiVersion": "v1" },
#   "dev": {
#     "baseUrl": "http://localhost:3000",
#     "apiKey": "dev-key-safe-to-commit"
#   },
#   "production": {
#     "baseUrl": "https://api.example.com",
#     "apiKey": "{{$processEnv PROD_API_KEY}}"
#   }
# }
#
# .http-client-env.local.json (IGNORE this):
# {
#   "dev": {
#     "apiKey": "my-personal-dev-key-override"
#   }
# }

# ============================================================================
# HTTP REQUEST FILES
# ============================================================================

# If you have sensitive requests with hardcoded data, ignore them
# (Better: use variables instead of hardcoding)
*.private.http
*.secret.http
*-local.http

# ============================================================================
# RESPONSE/HISTORY FILES (if you implement caching)
# ============================================================================

# Ignore cached responses (may contain sensitive data)
.rest-client-cache/
.http-client-history/

# ============================================================================
# BEST PRACTICES SUMMARY
# ============================================================================
#
# ‚úÖ DO:
# - Commit .http files with variables: {{apiKey}}, {{baseUrl}}
# - Commit environment files that use {{$processEnv}} for secrets
# - Use .env files for local development secrets (and ignore them)
# - Document required environment variables in README
#
# ‚ùå DON'T:
# - Commit .env files (they contain secrets)
# - Hardcode API keys, tokens, or passwords in .http files
# - Commit environment files with production secrets
# - Share personal API keys or credentials
#
# üîí SECURITY:
# - Use {{$processEnv VARIABLE}} for production secrets
# - Use {{$dotenv VARIABLE}} for development secrets
# - Keep .env files in .gitignore
# - Rotate any secrets that were accidentally committed
#
# ============================================================================
